Changing the name of a global variable in a project#

When we package the following code into an umd artifact and run it in the
browser, we can use the module via window.index.

export default () => {
  console.info('hello world');
};


** By default, the name of the source file is used as the name of the module's
global variable in the browser. **For the above example, the artifact would read
